-- Brazil's Cielo sees unit costs under control next year 
-- 
-- Wed Oct 29, 2014 12:40PM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, Oct 29 (Reuters) - Costs and expenses per transaction at Cielo SA <CIEL3.SA>, Brazil's biggest card payment processing company, will remain under control next year, Chief Executive Romulo Dias said on Wednesday.

Dias expects unit costs to decline in 2015 after rising to 0.77 reais per transaction in the third quarter and about 0.71 reais in average during the first half.